      "writtenOn": "2018-01-31T21:46:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "How about non-owned memory (associated with thread stacks)? That’ll be much trickier to solve, but it’s necessary for a complete fix. You should call that out here, and either point to the existing bug or have a new one on file for just this problem.\n\nLow-priority and it doesn’t need to happen in this change: given what we do elsewhere in Crashpad, I don’t think we’ll ever try to add extra memory based on something that points into some thread’s stack.",
      "revId": "dc681b6f74bcf72f9659840b48f45974ec12466e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
